Since $a_3 = a_1$, we have $a_3 = x$ and $a_2 = x$. Using the recursive relationship, we get:
\begin{align*}
a_4 &= \frac{1-x}{x},\\
a_5 &= \frac{1-a_4}{a_4} = \frac{1-\frac{1-x}{x}}{x/\left(1-x\right)} = \frac{x}{1-x-(1-x)} = \frac{x}{2-2x} = \frac{1}{2-x}\\
a_6 &= \frac{1}{2-a_5} = \frac{1}{2-\frac{1}{2-x}} = \frac{2-x}{3-x}\\
&\vdots \\
a_9 &= \frac{1}{1 - a_8} = \frac{1}{1 - \frac{2-x}{3-x}} = \frac{3-x}{2-x+x-x^2} = \frac{3-x}{1-x^2}
\end{align*}
